commit.message:
Convert all user-definable defvar into defcustom in bison-mode defgroup.

- Add the defgroup bison-mode, under the defgroup for C.
- All defcustom are in this new defgroup.
- This has no impact on users of Emacs 20 and later when defgroup and defcustom
  were introduced (in 1997).  Since the bison-mode.el was created in 1998, the
  probability that some users may be affected exists but is very low.
- Users can continue to set the variables as if they were declared as defvars.
  They can now use Emacs customization interface to control the values of the user-definable variables.
- Minor cleanup for the docstrings of the affected forms.
- Minor trailing whitespace removal.

Merge pull request #6 from petermoresi/master

Add support for jison
Automatically start bison-mode in .y and .l files.
Removing some unused, un-namespaced utility functinos.

Merge pull request #1 from syohex/fix-various-things

Fix various things

Fix calling function

Original code makes no sense and causes error.
Add autoload cookie for lazy loading

Correct for buffer local variables

Remove 'make-variable-buffer-local', because its usage is wrong and
'c-basic-offset' and 'c-offsets-alist' are already buffer-local
variables. And we should not use 'setq-default' because it effects
for other buffers.

Removing dependency on flex-mode.

We don't need it anyway, and it doesn't have licensing information.
Checking in the current state of bison-mode.
